US Realm laboratory result using CodeableConcept Data Type for non-numeric results

US Realm laboratory result using CodeableConcept Data Type for non-numeric results. Laboratory results to ordering providers in the ambulatory care setting and "reportable" laboratory test results to local public health agencies.

11/29/2014 EH : added extension for - specimen reject reason type = CodeableConcept - text OK valueSet v2 0490 for now. ( use when dataabsentreason equals - error - or code equals inconclusive etc ). Needs to be in context of obs since specimen may be suitable for some tests but not others.
Map to igs, review value set
CLIA require a reason when the test is not performed due to an unsatisfactory specimen

11/29/2014 EH : OBX.29Observation TypeIDR[1..1]1..6=HL70936 , added extension for - Kind of observation = Code - valueSet result = actual result, response = Responses to laboratory Ask at order (AOE) questions, information = other unsolicited clnically relevant information. ( taken from v 282). Required since drives operational functionality - question does it really.
11/19/2014 EH:OBX.3Observation IdentifierCWE_CRR[1..1]Laboratory Observation Identifier Value Set Use same structure as DO and DR name. See DAF comment 222,223
The use of the Logical Observation Identifiers Names and Codes (LOINC) code system is required where a LOINC code is available for the Observation.code, i.e. the being resulted.
The laboratory test that was performed. This is element is bound to LOINC.

UsageNote= The typical patterns for codes are: 1) a LOINC code either as a translation from a "local" code or as a primary code, or 2) a local code only if no suitable LOINC exists, or 3) both the local and the LOINC translation. Systems SHALL be capable of sending the local code if one exists
regex to LOINC invarient ( how create context for slice onlyhave lloyd check the regex

Used when the laboratory define how the dsplay text if different from the code display text.
This is the laboratory defined display text for the lab test if different from the code display text(s)
If this exists, this is the text to be used for display.
